# Claude Code Agent Repository Rules

# File Organization
- Always follow the structure defined in FILE_ORGANIZATION.md
- Place complete agents in agents/
- Reusable components go in subagents/
- Maintain README.md files in each directory

# Agent Development
- Test agents thoroughly before adding to repository
- Document agent capabilities and limitations
- Include example usage in documentation
- Follow naming conventions: kebab-case for files

# Code Quality
- Scripts must be executable and tested
- Include proper error handling
- Add comments for complex logic
- Validate all external dependencies

# Documentation Standards
- Update PROJECT_MAP.md when adding new agents
- Include real-world examples
- Document integration patterns
- Maintain version compatibility notes

# Collaboration
- Use pull requests for significant changes
- Review agent specifications before merging
- Test cross-agent compatibility
- Update documentation with changes